===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Garífuna'''

# An [[ethnic]] group in the [[Caribbean]] area, descended from a mix of [[Amerindian]] and [[African]] people, with many in Central America and the United States. 
# The [[language]] of the Garífuna people.

====Usage note====
Properly, the term '''Garífuna''' refers to the individual and the language, while Garinagu is the (plural or collective) term for the people.

